# CSS Organization

## Single source of truth

- Global styling lives in `src/app/globals.css`; load it only from `src/app/layout.tsx`.
- Fonts are registered in `src/app/lib/fonts.ts` via `next/font/google` with `variable: "--font-*"`.
- Root layout applies **every** font `.variable` class on `<body>` plus Tailwind utilities (`antialiased`, `min-h-screen`, `bg-screenWhite`, `font-body`).

## globals.css structure (preserve order and intent)

1. **`@import "tailwindcss"`** at the top.
2. **`@theme`** — custom breakpoints; keep `--breakpoint-*: initial` reset before defining `--breakpoint-3xs` … `--breakpoint-2xl`.
3. **`:root`** — semantic color tokens (`--primary`, `--screenWhite`, `--hoverNavLink`, etc.).
4. **`@theme inline`** — expose tokens to Tailwind: `--color-*`, `--font-title|subtitle|body|button|input|error` mapped to `var(--font-*)` CSS variables from fonts.
5. **`@layer base`** — reserved for future base resets (often empty).
6. **`@layer components`** — reusable UI classes (`whiteBox`, `btn`, form patterns, `loadingSpinner`, `navLink`). Prefer extending here when the same pattern repeats across routes.
7. **`@layer utilities`** — semantic one-off utilities (letter grades, assignment types, behavior bands). Keep names aligned with domain usage (grading/behaviors).
8. **`body`** — uses palette vars; default stack remains fallback in file unless intentionally changed.

## Fonts.ts rules

- One export per face; **`variable` must be `--font-<kebab>`** matching `@theme inline` (`--font-sour-gummy`, `--font-balsamiq-sans`, etc.).
- Export names are camelCase (`sourGummy`, `balsamiqSans`); import **all** used faces in `layout.tsx` and concatenate `.variable` on `<body>`.

## When to use what

- **Tailwind** — spacing, layout, one-off composition; use `bg-primary`, `text-screenWhite`, `font-title` from theme.
- **Component layer** — shared controls (`.btn`, `.formInput`, `.whiteBox`) and spinners.
- **Utilities layer** — domain-tinted status/grade classes only; do not duplicate in random CSS files.
- **New CSS file** — avoid unless a route truly needs isolated rules; if added, do not re-define tokens that belong in `globals.css`.

## Anti-patterns

- Importing `globals.css` outside root layout.
- Defining new colors outside `:root` / `@theme inline` without syncing Tailwind usage.
- Adding fonts in `fonts.ts` without wiring `.variable` on `<body>` and matching `--font-*` in `@theme inline`.
